y</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   LVL 27 MAGE</span><hr size=1> It may seem odd to have such a low lvl mage asking what spells he should be using, but I do not know if I am reaching my full potential atm. Anyways, I'm just wondering what spells I should have in my line up, and which summoning spells are the most usefull. Currently I am Using the follow:<br>
<br>
-My DD Spell (Fire Bolt I Believe)<br>
- I have the AE spell in my Book, but I rarely use it due to the fact that it gets me aggro<br>
- Obviously my pet spell and burnout spell<br>
- A free slot for anything i need(summoning spells, invis, see invis)<br>
-Renew summoning<br>
-Gate<br>
-Phantom Leather (cats eye agate is hard to find <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
- Summon Drink, Summon Food, Summon Bandages, Summon the current weapon, Invis, See invis<br>
<br>
What am i missing? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1890<br> <font color=#333333>(9/24/02 12:56:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1558.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LVL 27 MAGE</span><hr size=1> The most important spell you are missing right now is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Malise.htm">Malise</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  This is the first in an important spell line for mages.  As I recall, it might be frustrating this early in the game, with frequent resists, on the other hand with the new resist rules, it might well be worth while.  It lowers the target's resist against everything but disease by about 20 points.  Unlike the enchanter debuff line, this spell has low aggro.  Use it to pull, and the rest of you and your pet's spells will stick better.<br>
<br>
I do not recall how well <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Rain_of_Fire.htm">Rain of Fire</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> works, but later on rains can be an important spell for mages.  You might try at least playing with it now.<br>
<br>
If you are exploring the game for the first time and enjoy discovering things on your own, you might try out <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Spells/Eye_of_Zomm.htm">Eye of Zomm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to check out what's around corners or down the hall.<br>
<br>
At that level, I think I did <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The Icy Orcapades Starring Redwind</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, a temple in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  ForEverFrost</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with 5 shaman and one shadowknight orc, all 25ish and with a 6 minute timer.  Not soloable, but steady group experience, and decent cash, as they drop a lot of fine steel.  Relative easy commute from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Qeynos</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as well, for components, training and spells.<br>
<br>
Oh!  One last important thing.<br>
<br>
Build up your defensive skills <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>now</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> while you are young and your opponents are relatively less powerful.  Go ahead and take some beating, even solo.  It would build up your skills, give your pet a head start on aggro, save your pet some hitpoints, and make use of your natural hitpoint regeneration, which otherwise would be wasted.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
