<lj user=peacefulchaos> !</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualladdim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(9/25/02 12:44:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1558.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LVL 27 MAGE</span><hr size=1> You can always ask for some muzzle of mardu from high level mages. They are tradeable and 20% haste for your pet can help tons. Also ask for some summoned armor too as those helps a bit by giving your pet more AC. <br>
<br>
As a 60 mage these are my main stay spell during soloing. They may give you an idea on what to expect as you level up.<br>
<br>
Slot 1: Shock of Fiery blades - my main DD spell<br>
Slot 2: Cadeau of Flame - Single target damage shield<br>
Slot 3: Malosini - Malise line of spell (Very important)<br>
Slot 4: Some lvl 1 pull spell (I either use Burn or Flame bolt)<br>
Slot 5: Burnout IV - Burnout is very important<br>
Slot 6: Transons Elemental Infusion - Pet Heal (not very efficient but its useful)<br>
Slot 7: Pet spell<br>
Slot 8: Gate - Never leave home without it :P~<br>
<br>
Basically I buff up pet with burnout, then give it some weapons such as daggers and muzzle of mardu as well as a suit of phantom plate.<br>
<br>
Before pull, cast DS on pet (I usually use water or earth pet). Here you can either pull with malosi or with a pull spell. For long pulls i use flame bolt (very long range). As the mob approach, sick your pet on it, let pet and monster melee out about 10 seconds. Start nuking or use rain spell (which gets very economical on mana vs damage at high lvl). Rinse. Repeat.<br>
<br>
The malise line of spell is very important as it debuffs the mob. Once debuffed the mob is less likely to resist your spells. I use it when i solo or in group all the time. Resist = Wasted mana, at low level every mana counts.<br>
<br>
Burnout is important too as it gives a bit of AC, STR and Haste on pet. Although its not noticeable at low level, at high level (Burnout 4) there's a big difference between hasted and non-hasted pets. <p><p align="center"><a
